    "what_description": "Rehmannia glutinosa is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Plantaginaceae. It has a thick, fleshy rootstock and a taproot, which grows up to 5 cm in diameter, with a fibrous and reticulated rhizome. The stem is erect, 30-100 cm tall, with a simple or branched inflorescence and a green, lanceolate or ovate leaf. The flowers are purple, in a raceme or a spike, 5-20 cm long, with a tubular corolla and 5 lobes, and are fertile. The plant produces small, brown seeds, 3-5 mm long, in a capsule.",
