    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Rehmannia glutinosa are a group of iridoid glycosides known as rehmanniosides, which include rehmannioside A, rehmannioside B, rehmannioside C, rehmannioside D, and rehmannioside E. These compounds have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and immunomodulatory activities, contributing to the herb's traditional use in treating various diseases. Rehmannioside A has been found to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines, while rehmannioside B has been reported to exhibit antioxidant and free radical scavenging activities. Rehmannioside C has been shown to possess immunomodulatory effects by regulating the activity of immune cells, and rehmannioside D has been found to inhibit the expression of inflammatory genes. Rehmannioside E has been reported to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, and to possess a protective effect on the liver.",
