    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Rehmannia glutinosa are used to nourish the kidneys and tonify the blood, particularly in the treatment of deficiency patterns such as blood deficiency, kidney deficiency and yin deficiency. Liu wei dihuang wan is a classic formulation that combines Rehmannia glutinosa with other herbs to nourish the kidney and tonify the blood, while dang gui si ni tang is used to treat blood deficiency with amenorrhea or irregular menstruation by combining Rehmannia glutinosa with angelica and other herbs. Liu jun zi tang is another formulation that combines Rehmannia glutinosa with other herbs to tonify the kidney and promote urination, while sheng di huang tang is used to treat deficiency patterns with excessive sweating and night sweating. Si wu tang is a classic formulation that combines Rehmannia glutinosa with four other herbs to tonify the blood and nourish the liver and kidneys. These preparations are commonly used in traditional Chinese medicine to treat various deficiency patterns and promote overall health and well-being.",
