    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Rehmannia glutinosa are numerous and potentially severe when used improperly. Nausea is a common side effect due to its high content of iridoid glycosides and anthraquinones, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation and vomiting. Repeated use of Rehmannia glutinosa can exacerbate kidney damage in individuals with pre-existing kidney issues, as its saponins and glycosides can increase the risk of nephrotoxicity. Additionally, Rehmannia glutinosa can increase blood pressure and worsen anemia in individuals with hypertension or anemia, due to its ability to stimulate the sympathetic nervous system and reduce iron absorption. Furthermore, Rehmannia glutinosa can cause diarrhea in some individuals, potentially due to its laxative properties and irritation of the intestinal mucosa."
